Qatar, China Harbour to Sign $879 Million Contract, QNA Says

-- B y   R o b e r t   T u t t l e
-- 
2011-03-10T13:29:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/qatar-china-harbour-to-sign-879-million-contract-qna-says-1-.html
Qatar will sign a 3.2 billion-riyal
($879 million) contract with China Harbour Engineering Co. on
March 13 for the construction of the first phase of a new port
in the Gulf nation, the official  Qatari News Agency reported .  China Harbour will be responsible for digging a 17 meter-
deep basin and building quays and wave barriers, QNA said. The
14 billion-riyal port will be located near the country’s
southern industrial city of Mesaieed.  Qatar, the world’s biggest exporter of liquefied natural
gas, is upgrading its transport infrastructure before hosting
the 2022  World Cup . The nation is also building a $25 billion
rail and metro system, a new airport and a bridge linking the
country to Bahrain.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Robert Tuttle  in Doha at 
 rtuttle@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss on   sev@bloomberg.net  